{
  "stem": "10588.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We could not hold this [INAUDIBLE] separate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And in concentration camp was a law.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The worst offence any girl could do there was to take from another girl, because that was like taking life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That was the only time somebody stole from me-- the bread.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And Bina and I trusted each other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We kept our bread.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Some days when she had the worse day, I would give her a piece of mine, sometimes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But we did-- accepting of the friendship and the bread-- we both made a pledge to each other, to ourselves.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We're going to live and die with menschlichkeit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Everybody dies at one point or another.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So it's not just the quantity of life-- the quality.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Because we knew this is the only spiritual assistance that we could do.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we started do everything to sabotage.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We worked on the job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Unfortunately, at the beginning when we worked, the [INAUDIBLE] commander, which was-- used to call, like work outside-- useless work carrying stone or brick or gravel from one place to the other.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We couldn't-- there wasn't a lot to sabotage, but later on we did when there were other things that we could.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And Bina and I became inseparable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'd like to describe a day in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We would get up in the morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To begin with, we slept and worked, and wore the same clothes all the time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Every few months they would disinfect, because unfortunately, a lot of lice would set.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we really were worse than the Jews in Egypt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had all the plagues.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] A big pleasure was if you could undress the dress in time to clean off a little of the-- it's unfortunate it's very graphic, but I'm telling it as it is.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
